60.7	The_Hurt_Locker	The Hurt Locker	The Hurt Locker is a 2008 American war film about a three-man bomb disposal team during the Iraq War. The film was directed by Kathryn Bigelow and the screenplay was written by Mark Boal, a freelance writer who was embedded as a journalist in 2004 with a United States Army bomb squad in Iraq. It stars Jeremy Renner, Anthony Mackie, and Brian Geraghty.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/HLposterUSA2.jpg/220px-HLposterUSA2.jpg
